.SH NOTES
.sp
.LP
The default prompt for \fBcktime\fR is:
.sp
.in +2
.nf
Enter a time of day [?,q]:
.fi
.in -2
.sp

.sp
.LP
The default error message is:
.sp
.in +2
.nf
ERROR: Please enter the time of day.  Format is <format>.
.fi
.in -2
.sp

.sp
.LP
The default help message is:
.sp
.in +2
.nf
Please enter the time of day.  Format is <format>.
.fi
.in -2
.sp

.sp
.LP
When the quit option is chosen (and allowed), \fBq\fR is returned along with the return code \fB3\fR. The \fBvaltime\fR module will not produce any output. It returns  \fB0\fR for success and non-zero for failure.
